For these disparate "things" to communicate, a standardized language is indispensable. A variety of [communication protocols](/Communication_protocol) have emerged, each tailored to specific requirements regarding power consumption, range, and data throughput. The sheer number of these protocols, however, often contributes to the complexity and fragmentation that characterizes the current IoT landscape.

